    pearls: ["Hip precautions for POSTERIOR approach (most common): avoid Flexion >90 degrees, Adduction past midline, and Internal rotation -- mnemonic 'FAI'; use elevated toilet seat, abduction pillow between legs in bed, avoid low chairs, no crossing legs; maintain for 6-12 weeks until soft tissues heal","DVT is the most life-threatening early complication of TJA -- pharmacologic prophylaxis plus early mobilization plus SCDs form the triad of DVT prevention; patients undergoing THA should receive extended prophylaxis for 35 days (not just in-hospital)","Peroneal nerve palsy (foot drop) is the most common nerve injury after TKA -- assess ankle dorsiflexion at every neurovascular check; report inability to dorsiflex immediately; most cases are neuropraxia from positioning or edema and recover within 3-6 months","A post-TJA patient with fever >101.5F, persistent wound drainage, or increasing pain after initial improvement should be evaluated for periprosthetic infection -- check CRP and ESR, aspirate the joint for cell count and culture before starting antibiotics","Pre-operative MRSA decolonization (mupirocin nasal ointment + chlorhexidine body washes for 5 days) significantly reduces surgical site infection rates in colonized patients","Fat embolism syndrome presents 24-72 hours post-operatively with the classic triad: respiratory distress, neurological changes (confusion), and petechial rash over the upper chest and axillae -- it is distinct from PE and is treated with supportive care"],
