        rationale: "ANA is found in 5-15% of the general healthy population, particularly at low titers (1:40-1:80). In a patient with isolated joint pain and no systemic features of autoimmune disease, the positive ANA is most likely a false positive. This demonstrates the problem of ordering specific tests in low pre-test probability populations: the PPV is low even with a positive result. ANA should only be ordered when clinical features suggest systemic autoimmune disease."
