        correct: 1,
        rationale: "SnNOut: a test with high Sensitivity has very few false negatives, meaning if the test is Negative, the probability of disease is very low (it effectively rules Out the disease). This is why highly sensitive tests like D-dimer, high-sensitivity troponin, and 4th-generation HIV assays are used for screening and rule-out algorithms."
